  capable of proper performance of the motor task. In this study, we explored
  neural correlates of motor recovery in patients with stroke by investigating
  longitudinal changes in resting-state functional connectivity of the
  ipsilesional primary motor cortex (M1). METHODS: A longitudinal observational
