  oxygenation level-dependent (BOLD) and perfusion-based functional magnetic
  resonance imaging (fMRI) data is presented. In the proposed method,
  significant principal components are derived from noise regions-of-interest
  (ROI) in which the time series data are unlikely to be modulated by neural
