  leading to neurological deficits. However, advances in methods for assessing
  the human brain and in statistics have enabled new tools for the examination
  of the consequences of stroke on brain structure and function. Thereby, it
  has become evident that stroke has impact on the entire brain and its network
  properties and can therefore be considered as a network disease. The present
