  the brain; however, the spatial patterns of this reorganization remain
  largely unknown. METHODS: Using a large (N = 116) sample of participants who
  were in the chronic stages of stroke, we present a systematic study of the
  association between brain damage and functional connectivity within the
  intact hemisphere. We computed correlations between regional cortical damage
