  r=-0.68, p<0.05, FDR-corrected). Increasing dwell times, particularly those
  in a very segregated connectivity configuration, predicted higher acute
  stroke severity in our Bayesian modelling framework. Conclusions Our findings
  demonstrate transiently increased segregation between multiple functional
  domains in case of severe AIS. Dynamic connectivity involving default mode
