  surviving brain networks to compensate for damaged tissue. In rodent models,
  sensory and motor cortical representations have been shown to remap onto
  intact tissue around the lesion site, but remapping to more distal sites
  (e.g. in the contralesional hemisphere) has also been observed. Resting state
