  the extent of motor recovery in the early to late subacute phases, and
  furthermore, individuals with greater baseline motor impairment demonstrate
  more extensive early subacute functional reorganization (from one to two
  weeks post-stroke) and this reorganization correlates with better motor
  recovery at 6 months. Taken together, these results suggest that our graph
