    In this study, we have assessed the validity and reliability of an
  automated labeling system that we have developed for subdividing the human
  cerebral cortex on magnetic resonance images into gyral based regions of
  interest (ROIs). Using a dataset of 40 MRI scans we manually identified 34
  cortical ROIs in each of the individual hemispheres. This information was
  then encoded in the form of an atlas that was utilized to automatically label
  ROIs. To examine the validity, as well as the intra- and inter-rater
