  stroke-related disability from disability associated with general aging.
  Results showed that almost half (43\%) of all elderly stroke survivors in the
  cohort had moderate to severe neurological deficits. In the crude analyses,
  women were more dependent in ADLs (33.9\% vs 15.6\%), less likely to walk
