  and genetics. We provide evidence for biomarkers that are considered ready to
  be included in clinical trials, as well as others that are promising but not
  ready and so represent a developmental priority. We conclude with an example
  that illustrates the utility of biomarkers in recovery and rehabilitation
  research, demonstrating how the inclusion of a biomarker may enhance future
  clinical trials. In this way, we propose a way forward for when and where we
  can include biomarkers to advance the efficacy of the practice of, and
  research into, rehabilitation and recovery after stroke.%
