    Background. Accurate prediction of clinical impairment in upper-extremity
  motor function following therapy in chronic stroke patients is a difficult
  task for clinicians but is key in prescribing appropriate therapeutic
  strategies. Machine learning is a highly promising avenue with which to
  improve prediction accuracy in clinical practice. Objectives. The objective
