  stroke recovery. Several methods have been used to define CST damage and
  examine its relationship to motor performance, but which method is most
  useful remains unclear. Proprioceptive impairment also affects stroke
  recovery and may be related to CST damage. Methods. Robotic assessment
  quantified upper-limb motor and proprioceptive performance at 2 weeks and 6
  months poststroke (n = 149). Three previously-established CST lesion metrics
  were calculated using clinical neuroimaging. Diffusion magnetic resonance
  imaging quantified CST microstructure in a subset of participants (n = 21).
