  accuracy, using other (non-corticospinal tract) motor areas provided 87\%
  accuracy, and combining both resulted in 90\% accuracy. Conclusion This proof
  of concept approach highlights the relative importance of different
  anatomical structures in supporting post-stroke upper limb motor recovery and
  points towards methodologies that might be used to stratify patients in
  future restorative clinical trials.%
