    BACKGROUND AND PURPOSE: The Barthel Index (BI) and the Modified Rankin
  Scale (MRS) are commonly used scales that measure disability or dependence in
  activities of daily living in stroke victims. The objective of this study was
  to investigate how these scales were used and interpreted in acute stroke
  trials. METHODS: We identified from MEDLINE the major efficacy trials with
